Electrostatic charging and discharging in curation laboratories has the potential to cause damage to samples and equipment. In addition, electrostatic discharges are a serious safety hazard to laboratory personnel. Most curation cleanrooms maintain a temperature between 24 to 15∘C±1.0∘C\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
